  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a multinational, multicentre, randomised open-label, controlled, parallel-group phase&#xD;
      III study. Its aim is to demonstrate that a single intracoronary infusion of autologous bone&#xD;
      marrow-derived mononuclear cells is safe and reduces all-cause mortality in patients with&#xD;
      reduced left ventricular ejection fraction(&lt;/=45%) after successful reperfusion for acute&#xD;
      myocardial infarction when compared to a control group of patients undergoing best medical&#xD;
      care.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
